---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../data/site';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Contact"
  description="Corrections and contact information for Demon Born Compass."
  canonicalUrl="/contact/"
>
  <h1>Contact &amp; Corrections</h1>

  <p>
    To report a factual error, flag outdated information, or suggest a correction
    to any page on <strong>{SITE_TITLE}</strong>, follow the process below.
  </p>

  <div class="corrections-info">
    <h2>Correction submission process</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Identify the specific claim ID and page URL (found in the Sources registry or page source).</li>
      <li>Provide the official source that contradicts or updates the claim — patch notes, Roblox API data, or official developer statement are preferred.</li>
      <li>Describe the correction briefly — do not submit personal data or speculation.</li>
      <li>Submit via the contact channel provided at deployment. All corrections are reviewed against official sources before any page is updated.</li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0">
      <strong>Note:</strong> Corrections involving game mechanics, clan/breathing/class data,
      or active codes require official source evidence before any page will be updated.
      Community reports alone are not sufficient to change published facts.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>What to include in a correction</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Page URL and claim ID (if known)</li>
    <li>Current claim as written on the site</li>
    <li>Official source URL or description of the official source</li>
    <li>Proposed correction with explanation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What this site does not handle</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Game support requests — contact Roblox or the game developer directly</li>
    <li>Account issues, bans, or in-game purchases</li>
    <li>Requests to add codes from third-party sites (codes are only added from verified official sources)</li>
    <li>Requests to add tier lists, best builds, or breathing style guides (not in launch scope)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Response time</h2>
  <p>
    Corrections are reviewed during the operator's regular work hours (weekday evenings, UTC).
    Expect a response within 2–5 business days. Pages are not updated automatically —
    every change goes through a manual review against official sources.
  </p>

  <div class="info-note">
    <strong>No direct email is published here</strong> to avoid scraping.
    All correction workflows are handled through the deployment platform's built-in
    feedback channels at the preview URL.
  </div>
</ContentLayout>